.venv/
# YOUR private plan lives in config/personal/ — real financial data, never
# committed. The whole directory is ignored (so any file you drop in is safe by
# default); only its README is tracked. Create your plan by copying the tracked
# config.skeleton.yaml into it: cp config/config.skeleton.yaml config/personal/config.yaml
config/personal/*
!config/personal/README.md
# All of outputs/ is generated (regenerable via run.py); DECISIONS.md is the
# curated, versioned record of how the headline numbers moved. Ignore wholesale
# rather than only the top level — keeps scenarios/ out too (was inconsistent).
outputs/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
